## Definition

A _sifted $(\infty,1)$-colimit_ is an [[(âˆž,1)-colimit]] over a [[diagram]] that is a [[sifted (âˆž,1)-category]].

## Properties


+-- {: .num_prop }
###### Proposition

Let $C$ be an [[(âˆž,1)-category]] such that [[products]] preserve [[sifted (âˆž,1)-colimits]] (for instance an [[(âˆž,1)-topos]], see [[universal colimits]]).

Then [[sifted (âˆž,1)-colimits]] preserve finite products.

=--

This is ([Lurie, lemma 5.5.8.11](#Lurie)).

